      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">EU Conformity</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The Reality mentioned
in this manual conforms to the relevant requirements to the appropriate
EU Directive, i.e. that this Reality meets all relevant EU directives
and that it can be sold inside the European Union without national
commercial hindrances. </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The EU conformity, which is indicated
by means of the CE label on the name plate shall cease to be valid
if modifications are made to the equipment without the approval of
our company. </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Applied EU Directives: </b>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Electrical Equipment designed for use within certain Voltage
Limits (Low Voltage Directive) 2014/35/EU</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Electromagnetic Compatibility 2014/30/EU</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Applied Harmonised Standards:</b>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">EN 62040-1:2008/A1:2013 Safety requirements</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">EN 62040-2:2006/AC:2006 Electromagnetic compatibility (EMC)
requirements</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">EAC Conformity</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The Reality mentioned
in this manual conforms to the relevant requirements to the appropriate
EAC Directives, i.e. that this Reality meets all applicable TR CU
Directives and that it can be sold inside the customs union: Russia
– Belarus – Kazakhstan, without national commercial
hindrances. </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The EAC conformity, which is indicated by means
of the EAC label on the name plate shall cease to be valid if modifications
are made to the equipment without the approval of our company.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Applied Technical Regulations of the Customs Union (TR CU):</b>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">TR CU 004/2011 On Safety of Low Voltage Equipment</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">TR CU 020/2011 Electromagnetic compatibility on Technical Equipment</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Applied Harmonised Standards:</b>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">(ГОСТ Р) МЭК
62040-1-2013</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">МЭК 62040-2-2005</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">UL/CSA Conformity</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">If requested
Reality systems can be certified according to UL/CSA. Only applicable
for systems marked with the UL/CSA label.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The UL/CSA conformity,
which is indicated by means of the UL/CSA label on the name plate
shall cease to be valid if modifications are made to the equipment
without the approval of our company.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Applied Standards:</b>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">UL 1778 5th edition/CSA C22.2 No. 107.3, Uninterruptible Power
Systems</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">UL/CSA 60950-1 2nd edition, Information Technology Equipment
– Safety – Part 1: General Requirements</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
